            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. Lucius Cassius Hermes, best of men, lived for 60 years. His four children set this up for a deserving father.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
          <!--D.M.S. / L. Cassius / Hermes / optimus / virorum / vix.ann.LX / IIII f.p.p.m. Thus Lucius Cassius Hermes; the collocation optimus virorum is possibly unique, at least in Roman period. K follows Mommsen in thinking the number IIII in the final line is separate from the age, since numbers usually don't cross line breaks; K suggests resolving the last line as: IIII filii posuerunt patri merenti.-->
                </p>
            </div>
